# FIGMA MCP DESIGN SYSTEM COMPLIANCE

## CRITICAL RULES - NO EXCEPTIONS

### üö´ NEVER DO THESE:
- Hardcode hex colors: `#FFFFFF`, `#000`, `#2ABAA5`
- Hardcode RGB/RGBA: `rgb(42, 186, 165)`, `rgba(0,0,0,0.5)`
- Use brand colors with string notation: `"brand.white.100"`, `"brand.purple.300"`, `"brand.info.600"`, `"brand.success.50"`, `"brand.error.300"`, `"brand.warning.600"`
- Access brand colors via theme.palette: `theme.palette.brand.white[100]`, `theme.palette.brand.info[600]`, etc.
- Custom fontSize/fontWeight: `fontSize: "16px"`, `fontWeight: 600`
- Custom margin/padding: `margin: "8px"`, `padding: "16px"`
- Use sx prop for typography: `sx={theme => theme.typography.brandedH3}`
- Mix typography in Box components: `<Box sx={theme => theme.typography.medium}>`
- Use inline sx for complex styling: `sx={{ color: "primary.main", p: 2, "&:hover": {...} }}`
- Hardcode media queries: `@media (max-width: 768px)`, `@media (min-width: 1024px)`
- Create custom input components when branded ones exist
- Use Material-UI icons when react-feather has the same icon

